==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tittle
<hw>Tit"tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>titel</ets>,
<ets>titil</ets>, apparently a dim. of <ets>tit</ets>, in the sense of
small; cf. G. <ets>t⟦uum⟧ttel</ets> a tittle, dim. of OHG.
<ets>tutta</ets> teat. Perhaps, however, the same word as
<ets>title</ets>, n.]</ety> <def>A particle; a minute part; a jot; an
iota.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is easier for heaven and earth to pass, than one
<qex>tittle</qex> of the law to fail.</q> <rj><qau>Luke xvi.
17.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Every <qex>tittle</qex> of this prophecy is most exactly
verified.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tittlebat</ent>⟦br⟧
